SYNOPSIS
        string progress_meter(int iLength, int iHowMany, int iValue,
                     int iMaxValue, string sSymbol, string *asColors)

DESCRIPTION
        This will create a bar, of max length iLength, divided into
        iHowMany *equal* sections. Each section will be color-coded using
        asColors for each section, in the order provided. If a color is
        not provided for each section, it will cycle back to the first
        color provided. The returned string will only represent the
        percentage (iValue/iMaxValue) of the max length bar.

EXAMPLES
        progress_meter(20,4,75,100,"%",({ <C1>, <C2>, <C3> }))
           returns: "<C1>%%%%%<C2>%%%%%<C3>%%%%%"

        progress_meter(40,4,40,100,"%",({ <C1>, <C2>, <C3> }))
           returns: "<C1>%%%%%%%%%%<C2>%%%%%%"

        <Cn> being a color_code such as found in colorlist
